<title>FINLAND: FINLAND, SWEDEN FUND BALTIC LANGUAGE TEACHING.</title>
<headline>FINLAND, SWEDEN FUND BALTIC LANGUAGE TEACHING.</headline>
<dateline>HELSINKI 1997-03-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sweden and Finland said on Tuesday they are to provide funds to boost the learning of Estonian and Latvian by Russians living in the two countries and will also help to boost the security of Baltic state borders.</p>
<p>Finland is to provide 1.5 million markka to Estonia during 1997-1999 to boost the learning of Estonian by Russians while Sweden is to give 4.0 million krona in 1997-1998 for Latvian and Estonian language learning, the Finnish foreign ministry said in a statement.</p>
<p>It also said that both Sweden and Finland would give support to border controls in Latvia, Lithuania and Estonia.</p>
